 After Friday’s attack on Garkida in Adamawa State, residents of the community have been expressing fears over their safety. During the attack, at least two soldiers lost their lives while property worth millions of naira were destroyed. It was learnt Garkida residents are yet to recover from the shock as many still feel unsafe and planning to relocate to other areas. A hunter in the community, confirmed the killing of two soldiers and the burning of their patrol vehicles. He said, "Our people could not believe that these people (terrorists) would come and wreak havoc on us. “Many people want to relocate to Yola due to insecurity of lives and property. The government must take decisive action now." 